{
  "texts": [
    "Purified AAV libraries were injected intravenously (retro-orbital sinus) into four C57BL/6J adult female mice at a dose of 1 × 10 12 vg/ mouse (6-8 weeks of age).",
    "Two hours post-injection, serum was collected and tissues were harvested using disposable 3 mm biopsy punches (Integra, 33-32-P/25) with a new biopsy punch used per organ per replicate.",
    "Harvested tissues were immediately frozen on dry ice.",
    "AAV genomes were recovered using a DNeasy kit (Qiagen, 69504) following the manufacturer's protocol, and samples were eluted in 200 μL elution buffer for NGS preparation.",
    "The library administered had 100K unique amino acid variants following the Fit4Function criteria (uniformly sampled from the production-fit sequence space) in addition to a calibration set (3K), control variants, and AAV9."
  ]
}